und »disability« einer vergleichenden Analyse und decken die Gemeinsamkeiten ihrer Konstitutionslogik im Kontext des Sports auf.  aIn Sport, the categories of gender, ethnicity and disability are of particular significance. For instance, there is no other area of modern society with such an obvious and seemingly legitimate segregation in terms of gender and disability. Racism also remains a big issue in sport: although there is no longer a 'color line', ethno-national origin is still the primary characteristic used to form teams. This volume undertakes a comparative analysis of the social categories of gender, race and disability and reveals their constitutive logics and interactions in the context of sport.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDiscrimination in sports. 0aGender identity in sports. 0aRacism in sports. 0aSex discrimination in sports. 0aSportsxSociological aspects. 4aBehinderung. 4aEthnizität. 4aExklusion. 4aGender Studies. 4aKörper. 4aRassismus. 4aSegregration. 4aSoziologie. 4aSport. 4aSportwissenschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aBody.  aDisability Studies.  aEthnicity.  aExclusion.  aGender Studies.  aRacism.  aSociology.  aSport Science.  aSport.1 aDresen, Antje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeckemeyer, Karolin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHylton, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKläber, Mischa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Patrick B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Marion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Marion, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReemtsma, 